<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3135> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3135" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Didasc. Ter. And. (Donatus); see Dziatzko, RhM 21 (1866) 65f.; and Münzer, Gent. Val. 41, note 2, on Valerius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3134> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3134" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Dziatzko holds that these were Aediles at the time of a revival performance and is inclined to identify Valerius with the Consul of 131. Seidel (78) and Cichorius (Untersuch. Lucil. 235-237) use the combination of a plebeian and a patrician as an indication that the old rule of alternation had been given up. Dates and identifications remain exceedingly doubtful." .
